cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper is about unsupervised bilingual lexicon induction, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a regularization method to improve the performance of the models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for the models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance of the models using a standard benchmark, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.DL).
